{
  "id": "96735",
  "type": "Page",
  "tags": [],
  "title": "Probability Rules (10 of 11)",
  "content": {
    "bibrefs": [],
    "model": [
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "In our delivery example from a prior example, there are two categorical variables of interest in the background: "
              }
            ],
            "id": "c5ba07594ed04bbf99c61ea70bb9e44c",
            "type": "p"
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "children": [
                  {
                    "children": [
                      {
                        "text": "On-time delivery by service A (yes/no)"
                      }
                    ],
                    "id": "e7068af67d9e4624a8c7bd5641b312fc",
                    "type": "p"
                  }
                ],
                "id": "so6r0f8jv0grbha",
                "type": "li"
              },
              {
                "children": [
                  {
                    "children": [
                      {
                        "text": "On-time delivery by service B (yes/no)"
                      }
                    ],
                    "id": "b53b876ce10e4c9198661dcf3b660865",
                    "type": "p"
                  }
                ],
                "id": "7h6cduhpx05kuvq",
                "type": "li"
              }
            ],
            "id": "c31cb2ca45964998b5d1d50d1909b13f",
            "type": "ul"
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Since each of the two has two possible values (yes/no), there are four possible combinations altogether, which correspond to the four possible outcomes of using the two services."
              }
            ],
            "id": "f411d8dfec664db5aef0bc274d9ae0e9",
            "type": "p"
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "While the Venn diagrams were great to visualize the General Addition Rule, in cases like these it is much easier to display the information in and work with a two-way table of probabilities, much as we examined the relationship between two categorical variables in the Exploratory Data Analysis section."
              }
            ],
            "id": "d04b59da82d84de090a7074a9b1ea8f1",
            "type": "p"
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "How do we build a two-way table of probabilities? Let's use our delivery example to illustrate this simple process:"
              }
            ],
            "id": "d3f8db1495e04739b38363c67598bf01",
            "type": "p"
          },
          {
            "caption": [
              {
                "___selfClosing___": true,
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": " ",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ],
                "type": "p"
              }
            ],
            "children": [
              {
                "id": "y32lfvwbfp0udwu",
                "text": " ",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "controls": "true",
            "id": "d95ab0fb015e4347812d98f7f6a3e7a3",
            "src": "aN0eulm19MM",
            "type": "youtube"
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Now that we’ve completed the table, it is important to understand what each of the table’s entries mean in context. "
              }
            ],
            "id": "ef2c268b036f466da3e4acf63bd79438",
            "type": "p"
          },
          {
            "alt": "The table has columns \"B,\" \"not B,\" and \"Total.\" The rows are \"A,\" \"not A,\" and \"Total.\" Here are is some information about the table, organized by cell:         At the cell A,B, the value there (0.75) is P(A and B) = P(on-time delivery by both services).         At the cell A,not B, the value there (0.15) is P(A and Not B) = P(on-time delivery ONLY by service A).         At cell Not A and B, the value (0.05) is P(not A and B) = P(on-time delivery ONLY by service B).         At cell Not A and Not B, the value (0.05) is P(not A and not B) = P(Neither service A nor B delivered on time).",
            "caption": [
              {
                "___selfClosing___": true,
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": " ",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ],
                "type": "p"
              }
            ],
            "children": [
              {
                "id": "8c5qb3vh99apapo",
                "text": " ",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "id": "bbc2a4d57dc94aa2954b28e66b90dce6",
            "src": "https://d2xvti2irp4c7t.cloudfront.net/media/57/5752ad9e9eba50cfe6123499966cd7f2/prob_table_explained.png",
            "style": "inline",
            "type": "img",
            "vertical-align": "middle"
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "id": "wp6vu4h2c585ebx",
                "text": "Comment"
              }
            ],
            "id": "ykeh717cjn3dwpc",
            "type": "h1"
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "A common mistake is to confuse between: P(A) = P(event A occurs) and P(A and Not B) = P(ONLY event A occurs)[and similarly, between P(B) = P(event B occurs) and P(Not A and B) = P(only event B occurs)]. "
              }
            ],
            "id": "b19271b2f28843d7ad672622f1bf9c17",
            "type": "p"
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Looking at the probability table is a great way to clear-up this confusion:"
              }
            ],
            "id": "e44dd7dd6af541119e973a998470b4cd",
            "type": "p"
          },
          {
            "alt": "The table's first row has been highlighted. Here is the highlighted data in \"Row, Column\" format:         A, B:  P(A and B) = 0.75;         A, not B: P(A and not B) = 0.15;         A, Total: P(A) = 0.90 = P(A and B) + P(A and not B)",
            "caption": [
              {
                "___selfClosing___": true,
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": " ",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ],
                "type": "p"
              }
            ],
            "children": [
              {
                "id": "hg47jzhltggvacl",
                "text": " ",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "id": "b02b38354d084e5183c1d09d1cba540a",
            "src": "https://d2xvti2irp4c7t.cloudfront.net/media/58/58b37bd98e1ae202d3983208d0162088/prob_table.png",
            "style": "inline",
            "type": "img",
            "vertical-align": "middle"
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "P(A) = 0.90 means that in 90% of the cases when service A is used, it delivers the document on time. "
              }
            ],
            "id": "e557fb244499406fa180f280d5100232",
            "type": "p"
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "These cases of on-time delivery by service A can be decomposed into two sub-cases:"
              }
            ],
            "id": "d9d656fe04de4bb5862e14dcdc22a72a",
            "type": "p"
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "children": [
                  {
                    "children": [
                      {
                        "text": "P(A and B) = 0.75 → 75% of the time the document is delivered on time also by service B (i.e., the document is delivered on time by both services)"
                      }
                    ],
                    "id": "b75a0e08db914e188bdf2eeb0310bde2",
                    "type": "p"
                  }
                ],
                "id": "ibgj33wsw7fxhxw",
                "type": "li"
              },
              {
                "children": [
                  {
                    "children": [
                      {
                        "text": "P(A and Not B) = 0.15 → 15% of the time the document is not delivered on time by service B (i.e., delivered on time only by service A). "
                      }
                    ],
                    "id": "e04a9c3a44fb4560a6e2e8666b326ce1",
                    "type": "p"
                  }
                ],
                "id": "vi6776o0ad2cigz",
                "type": "li"
              }
            ],
            "id": "fe52853959e44939997522c0ed829d01",
            "type": "ul"
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Similarly,"
              }
            ],
            "id": "f5ec9e9a1d634c55af28932b92f0bcfc",
            "type": "p"
          },
          {
            "alt": "The table's first column has been highlighted. Here is the highlighted data in \"Row, Column\" format:         A,B:  P(A and B) = 0.75;         not A, B: P(not A and B) = 0.05;         B,Total: P(B) = 0.80 = P(A and B) + P(not A and B)",
            "caption": [
              {
                "___selfClosing___": true,
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": " ",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ],
                "type": "p"
              }
            ],
            "children": [
              {
                "id": "96lfbl13ubhcug6",
                "text": " ",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "id": "d69d295fb6cf4f94a4874ea71e4fd1fe",
            "src": "https://d2xvti2irp4c7t.cloudfront.net/media/78/7832166c6edd7c79bb16d7033729aac4/prob_table2.png",
            "style": "inline",
            "type": "img",
            "vertical-align": "middle"
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "P(B) = 0.80 means that in 80% of the cases when service B is used, it delivers the document on time. "
              }
            ],
            "id": "a858fc3d215f4144a0c1cfaac914d48f",
            "type": "p"
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "These cases of on-time delivery by service B can be decomposed into two sub-cases: "
              }
            ],
            "id": "f254b39de40e42a59787ca2fbc8e7880",
            "type": "p"
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "children": [
                  {
                    "children": [
                      {
                        "text": "P(A and B) = 0.75 → 75% of the time the document is delivered on time also by service A (i.e., the document is delivered on time by both services)"
                      }
                    ],
                    "id": "d6b96ddd63ec4ab0a6706b83190747dd",
                    "type": "p"
                  }
                ],
                "id": "7tt285j1n1bwdln",
                "type": "li"
              },
              {
                "children": [
                  {
                    "children": [
                      {
                        "text": "P(Not A and B) = 0.05 → 5% of the time the document is not delivered on time by service A (i.e., delivered on time "
                      },
                      {
                        "strong": true,
                        "text": "only by service B"
                      },
                      {
                        "text": ")."
                      }
                    ],
                    "id": "df64055541704636b82b3c7e94cfe518",
                    "type": "p"
                  }
                ],
                "id": "22pi6z8bkh2e7dy",
                "type": "li"
              }
            ],
            "id": "d6b78a7866ff4bb3a6a884b87c91da52",
            "type": "ul"
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "text": ""
              }
            ],
            "id": "80124976",
            "type": "p"
          }
        ],
        "id": "4080149768",
