        "layout": "vertical",
        "purpose": "learnbydoing",
        "type": "group"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "activity_id": 95863,
            "id": "895597988",
            "type": "activity-reference"
          }
        ],
        "id": "620843950",
        "layout": "vertical",
        "purpose": "didigetthis",
        "type": "group"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "id": "w4eur7etzd910xm",
                "text": "Comment"
              }
            ],
            "id": "hzf5u7mr2svp5fd",
            "type": "h1"
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "In both the delivery problem and the smoke detector problem, we knew P(A), P(B) and P(A and B). (In the smoke detector problem, we actually needed to work a bit to get P(A and B), but it wasn't too bad.) Visually, we had the probability for the three shaded cells below, which was enough information to complete the table."
              }
            ],
            "id": "d5fc34653c77472f82c8b12dc3b57cfd",
            "type": "p"
          },
          {
            "alt": "The table has columns \"B,\" \"not B,\" and \"Total.\" The rows are \"A,\" \"not A,\" and \"Total.\" We will be naming cells by \"{Row, Column}\" notation.         Cells {A,B}, {A, Total}, and {Total, B} have been shaded.",
            "caption": [
              {
                "___selfClosing___": true,
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": " ",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ],
                "type": "p"
              }
            ],
            "children": [
              {
                "id": "mb5ggyy6tgjl08k",
                "text": " ",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "id": "e98f51693d9848658a1b9a383a3d931d",
            "src": "https://d2xvti2irp4c7t.cloudfront.net/media/f7/f741efa34e7f58931f3fc457dbec3cf0/image031.gif",
            "style": "block",
            "type": "img",
            "vertical-align": "middle"
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "This, however, is not the only combination of three cells that would provide sufficient information to complete the table. Essentially, as long as we are given (or can calculate) one cell in each of the margins (the total row and column), and one of the four cells in the body of the table, we'll be able to complete the entire table. Visually, we need:"
              }
            ],
            "id": "b4b159a4a9854052b0a77a550b8361ee",
            "type": "p"
          },
          {
            "alt": "The same table. We need information about one of the cells in the body of the table. These cells are {A,B}, {A, not B}, {not A, B}, and {not A, not B}. In addition, we need information from one of the cells on the right margin. These cells are {A, Total} and {not A, Total}. The last group of cells we need information from is the bottom margin. These cells are {Total, B} and {Total, not B}. With one cell from each of these three groups we can fill in the entire table.",
            "caption": [
              {
                "___selfClosing___": true,
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": " ",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ],
                "type": "p"
              }
            ],
            "children": [
              {
                "id": "3s1gqmiqijlyrjx",
                "text": " ",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "id": "af2585f0dbd84212b07521cd1ee0645f",
            "src": "https://d2xvti2irp4c7t.cloudfront.net/media/4b/4b22114b92bda49cee8a3a06db0b0c7e/image032.gif",
            "style": "block",
            "type": "img",
            "vertical-align": "middle"
          }
        ],
        "id": "1357401132",
        "selection": {
          "anchor": {
            "offset": 0,
            "path": [
              0,
              0
            ]
          },
          "focus": {
            "offset": 0,
            "path": [
              1,
              0
            ]
          }
        },
        "type": "content"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Researchers studied thousands of court cases. For each case, they recorded the jury’s decision. In addition, they asked the judge in each case how he or she would have decided the same case if there were no jury. In 67% of the cases the jury voted to convict, in 83% of the cases the judge would have convicted, and in 19% of the cases only the judge would have convicted."
                  }
                ],
                "id": "c61930ac8269448b97bc483c5e058f7f",
                "type": "p"
              },
              {
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Let A be the event “jury convicts”."
                  }
                ],
                "id": "cc08040771c54117a2234e0378b28239",
                "type": "p"
              },
              {
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Let B be the event “judge convicts”."
                  }
                ],
                "id": "be99b27dc2a74487a0761a248ac1acd7",
                "type": "p"
              },
              {
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Complete the following table:"
                  }
                ],
                "id": "a8ee2d1c18b645a5afd96b618aca91c6",
                "type": "p"
              }
            ],
            "id": "3445261785",
            "selection": {
              "anchor": {
                "offset": 0,
                "path": [
                  0,
                  0
                ]
              },
              "focus": {
                "offset": 0,
                "path": [
                  1,
                  0
                ]
              }
            },
            "type": "content"
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
